## Diagnosis

The Input component's resting border is rendering at 2px when it should be 1px. The two-axis grammar (color channel + weight channel, paint-only ring on engaged) is architecturally correct but the token values on both axes are miscalibrated — the resting weight axis is set too heavy, and the engaged ring is likely not adding weight on top of a lighter base.

---

## Root Cause

**AP-072 — Token value drift under iterative patching.** Each successive fix adjusted structure without resetting the resting-weight token to its canonical hairline value. The engaged state added a ring correctly, but because the base was already 2px, the visual distinction collapsed.

The specific failure: `--input-border-width` (or equivalent resting token) was left at `2px` from a prior patch. The engaged ring then layers `2px` on top of `2px`, making both states identical in weight.

---

## Fix

### 1. Token definitions — `src/styles/tokens/components/input.css`

```css
/* ─── Input border tokens ─────────────────────────────────────────── */
/* Weight axis */
--input-border-width-rest:     1px;   /* hairline — was incorrectly 2px */
--input-border-width-engaged:  2px;   /* ring added on focus/active     */

/* Color axis */
--input-border-color-rest:     var(--color-neutral-300);
--input-border-color-engaged:  var(--color-accent-500);
--input-border-color-error:    var(--color-error-500);
--input-border-color-disabled: var(--color-neutral-200);
```

---

### 2. Component styles — `src/styles/components/input.css`

```css
.input {
  /* Weight axis: hairline at rest */
  border-width: var(--input-border-width-rest);     /* 1px */
  border-style: solid;
  border-color: var(--input-border-color-rest);

  /* Paint-only ring channel — zero at rest, no layout shift */
  outline: var(--input-border-width-rest) solid transparent;
  outline-offset: -1px;                              /* inset, not additive */
}

/* Engaged: weight axis steps up via outline, border holds color */
.input:focus-visible,
.input[data-state="focused"] {
  border-color: var(--input-border-color-engaged);
  /* Ring adds the second px — paint only, no reflow */
  outline-width: var(--input-border-width-engaged);  /* 2px */
  outline-color: var(--input-border-color-engaged);
}

/* Error: color axis only — weight stays at resting 1px unless engaged */
.input[data-state="error"] {
  border-color: var(--input-border-color-error);
}

.input[data-state="error"]:focus-visible {
  outline-width: var(--input-border-width-engaged);
  outline-color: var(--input-border-color-error);
}

/* Disabled: color axis only */
.input:disabled {
  border-color: var(--input-border-color-disabled);
  outline: none;
}
```

> **Why `outline` not a second `border`:** `outline` is paint-only — it does not participate in the box model, so toggling it between 0 and 2px at engagement causes zero layout shift. The border remains `1px` and owns the color channel; the outline owns the weight step. This is the correct implementation of the two-axis grammar.

---

### 3. Tailwind variant shim (if using utility classes) — `src/components/ui/Input.tsx`

```tsx
const inputVariants = cva(
  [
    // Weight axis — resting hairline
    "border border-neutral-300",          // border = 1px solid

    // Ring channel — transparent at rest, paint-only
    "outline outline-1 outline-transparent outline-offset-[-1px]",

    // Engaged: ring steps to 2px, color flips
    "focus-visible:border-accent-500",
    "focus-visible:outline-2 focus-visible:outline-accent-500",

    "disabled:border-neutral-200 disabled:outline-none",
  ],
  {
    variants: {
      error: {
        true: [
          "border-error-500",
          "focus-visible:outline-2 focus-visible:outline-error-500",
        ],
      },
    },
  }
);
```

---

## Principle

**Two-axis border grammar — canonical values:**

| State    | Weight channel (`border-width`) | Ring channel (`outline-width`) | Color channel |
|----------|---------------------------------|--------------------------------|---------------|
| Rest     | `1px`                           | `0` (transparent)              | neutral       |
| Engaged  | `1px` (unchanged)               | `2px`                          | accent        |
| Error    | `1px` (unchanged)               | `2px` on focus                 | error         |
| Disabled | `1px` (unchanged)               | none                           | muted         |

The border holds position and color. The outline holds perceived weight at engagement. Neither axis should be patched in isolation — changing one without resetting the other is exactly what produced the 2px resting state across four iterations. Lock these values as a paired unit in the token file; patch the token file, not the component.
